# Cache headers for prefetching support in Firefox and Safari
# See: https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/prefetch/#firefox
# 
# Firefox requires explicit cache headers (Cache-Control or Expires) or ETag
# Safari requires Cache-Control, Expires, and ETag (ETag set automatically by Cloudflare)
#
# max-age=0 with must-revalidate allows browsers to cache but validate with ETag
# This enables prefetching while ensuring fresh content

# Apply to all HTML pages (Astro generates clean URLs without .html extension)
/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate

